investment_performance: Total Value to Paid-In Capital (TVPI): 1.32x
Distributions to Paid-In Capital (DPI): 0.00x
Fund had a net mark up in Q3, with two portfolio company mark ups and four markdowns.
Net unrealized gain for Q3 was $4,797,852, while year-to-date net unrealized loss was $(1,650,363).
Precision Medication was marked up in Q3 to $16,312,497 from $9,062,499, now valued at 11.25x cost.
Revi Technologies ended Q3 with a $16M revenue run rate, up from $13.8M in Q2 and $8.4M a year ago.
Elife Tech ended Q3 with $17M ARR, up from $14.25M in Q2, and raised a small inside round at a $100M post-money valuation.
Benefitbay ended Q3 with ~$7M of contracted ARR, expecting ~$10M contracted ARR by year-end, representing ~150% ARR growth.
Techmate posted its strongest quarter ever in Q3, generating $1.33M in revenue (up 38% year-over-year) and $64K EBITDA.
Wherefour grew ARR to $2.84M in Q3, up from $2.75M in Q2, with cash flow roughly breakeven.
HAAS Alert ended Q3 with $8.6M contracted ARR, up 42% YoY and 10% QoQ.
Sware ended Q3 at $3.4M ARR, up 27% YoY, with $192K in new bookings.
Upflex ended Q3 with $4.0M in net ARR, up from $3.3M a year ago.
Aiden Technologies ended Q3 roughly flat at ~$4.2M ARR due to slipped deals and loss of two enterprise accounts.
Bullpen Sports Network (Wave) posted $9.48M in Q3 revenue, a temporary dip, but expects its strongest revenue quarter ever in Q4.
Goldfish Social (Cohley) had a flat Q3, with new sales neutralized by down sells from existing customers, but remains strongly EBITDA positive.
SocialHP had a stable Q3, with MRR essentially flat at $109K, low churn at 1.7%, and posted profits.
Qeepsake's position is valued at 50% of cost due to an asset sale to Tinybeans Group Ltd.
ForwardLane's position was marked down in Q3 to $500,000 from $750,000.
Stage Meta's position was marked down in Q3 to $350,000 from $700,000.
Lateral Technology improved ARR in Q3 to ~$1.2M, up from $1M in Q2, but its position is held at 50% of cost.
Sayge's position was written off in Q4 2023.
Vertify's position was marked to $0 due to an asset sale where investors will not receive proceeds.
Unboxt's position value is $0 as it transitioned to a self-funded model and is winding down operations.
Careteam Technologies' ARR held steady at ~$790K CAD, but its position is held at 50% of cost due to uncertainty.
Maya AI experienced significant churn in Q3, ending at ~$30k MRR due to a flawed unlimited usage business model.
key_takeaways: Fund-level TVPI is 1.32x and DPI is 0.00x as of Q3 2025, indicating early-stage growth with no distributions yet.
Precision Medication achieved a significant markup (11.25x cost) and is positioned for market dominance in D2C compounding.
Revi Technologies and Elife Tech demonstrated strong ARR growth and successful funding rounds/new product developments.
Benefitbay is on track for substantial ARR growth (150%) by year-end, establishing a strong niche in enterprise ICHRA administration.
Techmate continues to show strong financial performance with record revenue and profitability.
Several portfolio companies (Sayge, Vertify, Unboxt) have been written off or marked to $0, reflecting typical venture capital portfolio dynamics.
Multiple companies (Careteam, ForwardLane, Stage Meta, Lateral Technology, Maya AI, Averi) faced performance challenges, leading to markdowns or markdown watch.
business_updates: The Fund made follow-on investments into Benefitbay and Hello Hero in Q3.
Elife Tech developed and successfully tested new ridesharing technology, signing 6+ large consumer brands as channel partners.
Benefitbay is building a strong brand as 'ICHRA for Enterprise' by mastering complex conversions for large employers.
Qeepsake is undergoing an asset sale to Tinybeans Group Ltd, with an all-stock deal and a 24-month lockup.
Vertify is completing an asset sale, with no proceeds expected for investors.
Unboxt transitioned to a self-funded model, winding down operations while maintaining the platform as a free service.
ForwardLane is focused on the development and launch of its new platform, which will determine future growth.
Stage Meta is pivoting its technology to be the Teleport Plaque Address (TPA) for AI agents due to slower-than-expected uptake in other markets.
Elidah submitted Elitone for Men to the FDA and reopened its Series A to support reimbursement expansion and global distribution.
HAAS Alert is closing a $3M-$4M Series A extension to extend runway through 2026.
Maya AI is exploring new product pricing and lead sourcing to address its flawed unlimited usage business model.
Precision Medication is building out large new facilities in NY and CA, supported by a substantial cash balance and credit line.
Sware is positioning to move upmarket and reduce reliance on volatile SMB biotech customers by delivering enterprise-grade capabilities.
Upflex is working to bring its ~$210K monthly net burn towards breakeven and has a massive pipeline for its product.
Upswot's asset sale to Uptiq closed in January 2025, with the Fund receiving preferred stock in Uptiq.
OLIMP is waiting for the extended trucking and logistics recession to end, anticipating $14M in GMV for the year.
Influence Mobile is right-sizing its team and launched a new AI-driven bidding engine to improve user-acquisition profitability.

L Squared Case (with M&A) forecasts revenue of $199M and Adj. EBITDA of $67M by 2030E
Organic returns of 16% IRR / 2.1x MOIC
Total Revenue CAGR 2025-2030: 26%
Adj. EBITDA CAGR 2025-2030: 26%
Gross Profit Margin 2025: 49.7%
Adj. EBITDA Margin 2025: 33.8%
Entry price of $305M represents 13.8x LTM 3/31/2026E and 12.2x 2026E Adj. EBITDA
Transaction financed via $191.75M L Squared / Co-invest Equity, $10M Management Rollover, and $115M Term Loan
Term Loan: $115M (5.5x 2025 Adj. EBITDA) at SOFR+450bps
Total Net Leverage covenant of 9.25x provides significant cushion throughout the hold period
NPD revenue increased to ~5% in 2025, with a management goal to achieve ~10% by 2030
Identified upside opportunities include $1.3M incremental pricing, $0.3M Vertiv volumes, and $4M Veris opportunity for 2026E EBITDA
Pricing expected to drive ~60% of 2026P revenue growth and ~85% of 2026P EBITDA growth
key_takeaways: FDI is a leading designer and manufacturer of essential devices for power, sensing, and control in building automation systems.
The company is led by an exceptional, proven leadership team with extensive experience.
Over 75% of FDI’s demand is driven from Retrofit & Replacement (R&R).
FDI offers a portfolio of low ASP, high cost of failure components.
The company is well positioned to capture growth from macro tailwinds such as aging infrastructure, electrification, and data centers.
FDI surpasses competitors on value indicators like reliability, customer care, and lead times, while offering competitive pricing.
Strong customer retention and long-tenured revenue base, with an average top 10 customer tenure of 20+ years.
FDI's "Relay-in-a-Box" (RIB) is an industry-leading brand known for quality, reliability, and ease of installation.
Significant M&A opportunities exist in adjacent product lines and end markets.
L Squared has a proven track record of creating value in businesses similar to Functional Devices.
L Squared plans to supplement management, recruit value-added board members, invest in new product development, drive targeted pricing increases, and pursue M&A.
High visibility into 2026P results is driven by repeat customer orders from long-tenured customers with little sensitivity to price increases.
FDI maintains a strong safety record with TRIR generally at or below industry averages and low DART rates.
Employee satisfaction is above average for the industry, with competitive compensation and benefits.
business_updates: FDI sells primarily via distributors to blue-chip OEMs and end customers.
The market for peripheral components is attractive and growing, supported by aging commercial infrastructure, rapid acceleration in US energy consumption, and AI adoption fueling data center growth.
Multiple levers for growth include organic growth (market tailwinds, wallet share expansion, pricing upside, new product development) and M&A.
L Squared plans to implement AI initiatives to improve sales organization efficiency via data analysis and synthesis.
Veris is deprioritizing production of its branded current sensors and relays, creating a potential white-label opportunity for FDI.
FDI recently secured a new opportunity to supply critical components for Vertiv's Power Distribution Units (PDUs).
A new data center OEM program via Trane Technologies involves FDI supplying current sensors for their Cooling Distribution Unit line.
Data centers constitute ~15-20% of today’s commercial building market and are experiencing rapid growth due to AI adoption.
Demand for FDI’s components is consistently driven by aging building infrastructure and ongoing retrofit, renovation, and maintenance work.
Product development has been re-prioritized with key hires and an accelerated focus on new product innovation.
L Squared has identified 228 high-priority M&A targets across the fragmented peripheral components and sensors market.
There is a significant opportunity for Serviceable Addressable Market (SAM) expansion through Core FDI SAM growth, New Product Development, and M&A.
Key risks identified include potential "overstocking" by end customers, customer concentration, tariffs, and M&A execution, with mitigating factors in place.
The transaction is anticipated to sign on January 30th, 2026, with capital calls in early to mid-February and closing estimated for late February 2026.
A third-party environmental review indicates FDI's facilities have a limited environmental impact and pose a low risk.

key_takeaways: A capital call is being sought to address near-term liquidity needs created by sustained operating cash burn, accrued liabilities, and financing-related obligations.
The REIT must address a maturing line of credit, upcoming interest rate cap and escrow obligations, deferred maintenance needs, and other accrued payables.

The capital raise is intended to provide sufficient runway to meet obligations, avoid distressed asset sales in a soft market, and allow the portfolio time to benefit from an improving supply-demand backdrop.
The capital is not intended to fund new acquisitions or growth initiatives; the focus is stabilization, liquidity, and preservation of existing value.
The capital call is structured as a senior preferred investment at the REIT level with an 18% annual compounded preferred return, coupled with equity warrants.
Participating investors will receive penny warrants, providing the right to acquire approximately 75% of the fully diluted equity at liquidation, significantly diluting non-participating investors.
Trinity recommends that Converted Mezzanine Investors strongly consider participation (20-50% of invested capital) to avoid a likely loss of capital.
Trinity advises Common Equity / Founder’s Share Investors to evaluate participation cautiously, as equity remains at risk under most scenarios.

The minimum capital raise required to close is $30 million, which would address immediate liquidity needs but leave the portfolio vulnerable to continued operating volatility.

If the full $70 million is raised, Trinity expects the REIT to fully address liquidity, eliminate the risk of forced asset sales, maintain operational continuity, and allow time for market fundamentals to improve.
S2 has stated they can no longer support the portfolio solely through sponsor capital, making investor support critical to avoid an accelerated wind-down.
